15/*! \file */
16#include <config.h>
17
18#include <isc/log.h>
19#include <isc/mem.h>
20#include <isc/print.h>
21#include <isc/util.h>
22
23#include <dns/journal.h>
24#include <dns/log.h>
25#include <dns/result.h>
26#include <dns/types.h>
27
28#include <stdlib.h>
29
30/*
31 * Setup logging to use stderr.
32 */
33static isc_result_t
34setup_logging(isc_mem_t *mctx, FILE *errout, isc_log_t **logp) {
35 isc_logdestination_t destination;
36 isc_logconfig_t *logconfig = NULL;
37 isc_log_t *log = NULL;
38
39 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_log_create(mctx, &log, &logconfig) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
40 isc_log_setcontext(log);
41 dns_log_init(log);
42 dns_log_setcontext(log);
43
44 destination.file.stream = errout;
45 destination.file.name = NULL;
46 destination.file.versions = ISC_LOG_ROLLNEVER;
47 destination.file.maximum_size = 0;
48 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_log_createchannel(logconfig, "stderr",
49 ISC_LOG_TOFILEDESC,
50 ISC_LOG_DYNAMIC,
51 &destination, 0) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
52 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_log_usechannel(logconfig, "stderr",
53 NULL, NULL) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
54
55 *logp = log;
56 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
57}
58
59int
60main(int argc, char **argv) {
61 char *file;
62 isc_mem_t *mctx = NULL;
63 isc_result_t result;
64 isc_log_t *lctx = NULL;
65
66 if (argc != 2) {
67 printf("usage: %s journal\n", argv[0]);
68 return(1);
69 }
70
71 file = argv[1];
72
73 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_mem_create(0, 0, &mctx) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
74 RUNTIME_CHECK(setup_logging(mctx, stderr, &lctx) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
75
76 result = dns_journal_print(mctx, file, stdout);
77 if (result == DNS_R_NOJOURNAL)
78 fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", dns_result_totext(result));
79 isc_log_destroy(&lctx);
80 isc_mem_detach(&mctx);
81 return(result != ISC_R_SUCCESS ? 1 : 0);
82}
